00:06:28.565 --> 00:06:30.200
CORI ELLISON: How
do I become one?

00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:32.000
Well, with great difficulty.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.800
I was just saying to my friends
here that there currently

00:06:36.800 --> 00:06:40.070
exists no training program
in North America for opera

00:06:40.070 --> 00:06:41.240
dramaturgs.

00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:45.020
And I'm in the process of
creating one for American Lyric

00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:46.100
Theater in New York.

00:06:46.100 --> 00:06:51.140
But to answer your question, an
opera dramaturg, or a dramaturg

00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:54.800
in general in the context
of developing a new work

00:06:54.800 --> 00:07:01.760
is a person who works with
the composer and librettist.

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:05.019
And the first thing is
to really understand

00:07:05.019 --> 00:07:07.310
what it is they're trying to
do, the piece that they're

00:07:07.310 --> 00:07:11.570
trying to create, and
to help them do that.

00:07:11.570 --> 00:07:17.302
And it sounds like a
no-brainer sort of no-show job

00:07:17.302 --> 00:07:18.260
or something like that.

00:07:18.260 --> 00:07:22.250
But often it's not,
because artists

00:07:22.250 --> 00:07:24.680
have very distinct visions.

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:26.930
And a composer
and librettist may

00:07:26.930 --> 00:07:30.620
come to the same project
with different visions

00:07:30.620 --> 00:07:32.990
because of just who they are.

00:07:32.990 --> 00:07:39.740
So the trick is-- without at
all imposing my own opinions

00:07:39.740 --> 00:07:45.830
about it-- to try to bring them
together and show them where

00:07:45.830 --> 00:07:47.240
they're really intersecting.

00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:48.740
And maybe they don't
think they are.

00:07:48.740 --> 00:07:54.114
But just really
help the project--

00:07:54.114 --> 00:07:55.280
BOB CORNWALL: Come together.

00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:59.840
CORI ELLISON: --gel by helping
the artists gel together.

00:07:59.840 --> 00:08:05.660
And that boils down to big
aspects of the piece, details,

00:08:05.660 --> 00:08:08.420
lots of different
things along the way.

00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:13.310
And then of course, when Peter
Hinton joined in as director,

00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:18.260
