existing repertory of operas.

00:09:06.890 --> 00:09:10.970
And that's really helped me work
with composers and librettists

00:09:10.970 --> 00:09:13.040
of today.

00:09:13.040 --> 00:09:16.970
Because the best
teachers, in a way,

00:09:16.970 --> 00:09:20.360
are the great composers
and librettists like Mozart

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:23.810
and Da Ponte or Verdi and Boito.

00:09:23.810 --> 00:09:28.250
And there's no challenge that
a composer and librettist

00:09:28.250 --> 00:09:32.125
of today is going to encounter
that a great composer

00:09:32.125 --> 00:09:33.710
and librettists of
the past didn't.

00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:38.220
So often, when you're
trying to solve a problem,

00:09:38.220 --> 00:09:42.680
you'll go to a model in
the standard repertory

00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:45.440
and say, look at
what these folks did

00:09:45.440 --> 00:09:47.230
with the same challenge.

00:09:47.230 --> 00:09:49.540
BOB CORNWALL: Yeah,
