00:56:59.890 --> 00:57:02.540
And then tomorrow, I'll go
in and continue to work.

00:57:02.540 --> 00:57:06.180
So I do feel good.

00:57:06.180 --> 00:57:08.950
And today has been very
interesting for me,

00:57:08.950 --> 00:57:12.850
because I got up this
morning exhausted.

00:57:12.850 --> 00:57:16.600
And to come to events to
talk about what we're doing

00:57:16.600 --> 00:57:19.330
has been healing for me.

00:57:19.330 --> 00:57:24.040
It's been really good for my
spirit to be with my creators

00:57:24.040 --> 00:57:25.840
and to talk about
what we've been doing.

00:57:25.840 --> 00:57:28.240
Because it's so busy there.

00:57:28.240 --> 00:57:31.060
Like, I had this moment
last night after the dress,

00:57:31.060 --> 00:57:33.910
where when it came down and
the curtain call was finished,

00:57:33.910 --> 00:57:38.260
I saw Cori and Rufus embrace.

00:57:38.260 --> 00:57:39.589
And I went, oh, that's so nice.

00:57:39.589 --> 00:57:41.380
Because it was the
first time I'd seen them

00:57:41.380 --> 00:57:43.390
after running something
that they didn't have

00:57:43.390 --> 00:57:45.270
10 million notes that they--

00:57:45.270 --> 00:57:46.160
[LAUGHTER]

00:57:46.160 --> 00:57:47.030
--towards me.

00:57:47.030 --> 00:57:50.500
And I went-- that you
could actually go--

00:57:50.500 --> 00:57:51.730
we did something.

00:57:51.730 --> 00:57:52.934
That was so gratifying.

00:57:52.934 --> 00:57:53.850
BOB CORNWALL: Totally.

00:57:53.850 --> 00:57:56.030
PETER HINTON: So that's what I
hope to be doing tomorrow night

00:57:56.030 --> 00:57:56.930
when it's over.

00:57:56.930 --> 00:57:57.435
BOB CORNWALL: Amazing.

00:57:57.435 --> 00:57:58.518
PETER HINTON: Is be in a--

00:57:58.518 --> 00:57:59.110
[SIGHING]

00:57:59.110 --> 00:57:59.590
BOB CORNWALL: Perfect.

00:57:59.590 --> 00:58:00.360
AUDIENCE: In an embrace.

00:58:00.360 --> 00:58:00.910
PETER HINTON: In an embrace.

00:58:00.910 --> 00:58:02.330
BOB CORNWALL: In an
embrace, I love that.

00:58:02.330 --> 00:58:02.830
Cori?

00:58:02.830 --> 00:58:05.370
CORI ELLISON: Well, I'm
Cori, the dramaturg.

00:58:05.370 --> 00:58:07.510
[LAUGHTER]

00:58:07.510 --> 00:58:10.660
And the last couple
of weeks have

00:58:10.660 --> 00:58:12.400
been sort of a roller coaster.

00:58:12.400 --> 00:58:16.030
I mean, there have been
moments where all you can see

00:58:16.030 --> 00:58:20.340
is how much there
still remains to do.

00:58:20.340 --> 00:58:22.300
And then there are
moments where you just

00:58:22.300 --> 00:58:28.300
sit back and feel like, wow,
the effect that this is creating

00:58:28.300 --> 00:58:29.360
is tremendous.

00:58:29.360 --> 00:58:31.660
And I do, at this
point, especially

00:58:31.660 --> 00:58:34.690
after last night's
final dress rehearsal,

00:58:34.690 --> 00:58:38.590
I feel tremendous
confidence in the fact

00:58:38.590 --> 00:58:43.690
that the audience is going
to be really deeply moved.

00:58:43.690 --> 00:58:47.050
Because that's certainly what
we experienced last night.

00:58:47.050 --> 00:58:52.450
It was a beautiful
feeling to just feel

00:58:52.450 --> 00:58:55.000
the vibe in the place.

00:58:55.000 --> 00:58:59.080
And so afterwards, I
expect to feel relieved,

00:58:59.080 --> 00:59:02.890
to feel celebratory, maybe
give Rufus another big hug.

00:59:02.890 --> 00:59:04.610
[LAUGHTER]

00:59:04.610 --> 00:59:06.160
BOB CORNWALL: That
sounds amazing.

00:59:06.160 --> 00:59:07.350
And Isaiah?

00:59:07.350 --> 00:59:12.550
ISAIAH BELL: Well, every step
of this from when I first

00:59:12.550 --> 00:59:15.480
cracked the score to when we had
the first rehearsal, and people

00:59:15.480 --> 00:59:17.200
are first hearing it
that aren't just me

00:59:17.200 --> 00:59:20.790
and my coaches, to the
first staging rehearsal,

00:59:20.790 --> 00:59:22.649
to the first rehearsal
with orchestra,

00:59:22.649 --> 00:59:24.940
and then of course last night,
which was the first time

00:59:24.940 --> 00:59:26.560
that a wider audience saw it--

00:59:26.560 --> 00:59:31.870
every time you think,
OK, this is another step.

00:59:31.870 --> 00:59:36.730
And each time, you're aware
that it's a new hurdle

00:59:36.730 --> 00:59:41.440
to overcome, and also hopefully,
that it's a new sort of arrow

00:59:41.440 --> 00:59:43.480
in your quiver of
telling yourself

00:59:43.480 --> 00:59:44.620
that it's going to be fine.

00:59:44.620 --> 00:59:46.340
[LAUGHTER]

00:59:46.340 --> 00:59:49.510
But the thing
about performing it

00:59:49.510 --> 00:59:52.194
is that so much of
your work, of course,

00:59:52.194 --> 00:59:54.610
is preparation, and all the
work that we've done together,

00:59:54.610 --> 00:59:57.520
and all the discussions we've
had, and all the workshopping.

00:59:57.520 --> 01:00:02.200
But the bulk of the work,
really, at this point

01:00:02.200 --> 01:00:06.880
is making sure that
your living energy

01:00:06.880 --> 01:00:10.780
is ready to be the instrument
in the moment from show to show.

01:00:10.780 --> 01:00:15.832
As you know, as
performers, so you

01:00:15.832 --> 01:00:18.290
can never feel-- like you ask
about celebration afterwards.

01:00:18.290 --> 01:00:23.390
Like of course, if it's a
big success, which we all

01:00:23.390 --> 01:00:26.690
expect and hope that it will
be, you're going to be relieved,

01:00:26.690 --> 01:00:28.160
and you're going
to have a drink.

01:00:28.160 --> 01:00:31.190
My husband's here, and a whole
bunch of my friends are coming.

01:00:31.190 --> 01:00:34.340
But you'll also be looking
forward to the next show,

01:00:34.340 --> 01:00:36.877
and you're not going to be going
out to the bar till 4:00 AM

01:00:36.877 --> 01:00:37.460
and screaming.

01:00:37.460 --> 01:00:39.950
Because the whole process
has to start again

01:00:39.950 --> 01:00:41.750
for me for every show.

01:00:41.750 --> 01:00:44.921
Because really, no matter how
many hurdles you've overcome--

01:00:44.921 --> 01:00:46.670
and of course, at this
point in your life,

01:00:46.670 --> 01:00:50.960
to get to this you've done a lot
of work for every step that you

01:00:50.960 --> 01:00:52.496
go past--

01:00:52.496 --> 01:00:53.870
every time you
step on stage, you

01:00:53.870 --> 01:00:55.110
have to do it all over again.

01:00:55.110 --> 01:00:56.901
And you have to make
it new all over again.

01:00:56.901 --> 01:01:02.105
And your aliveness is the
string that you're playing on.

01:01:02.105 --> 01:01:03.230
BOB CORNWALL: That's great.

01:01:03.230 --> 01:01:06.280
Well, know that we
are all behind you.

01:01:06.280 --> 01:01:08.180
And we are sending
positive vibes

01:01:08.180 --> 01:01:09.560
supporting you in this moment.

01:01:09.560 --> 01:01:13.040
And we all hope that
tomorrow, in that moment when

01:01:13.040 --> 01:01:16.800
the curtain closes, that feeling
is exactly what you described

01:01:16.800 --> 01:01:18.810
today, and it's
just as delicious

01:01:18.810 --> 01:01:20.930
as it can absolutely get.

01:01:20.930 --> 01:01:23.390
So thank you very much
for joining us today.

01:01:23.390 --> 01:01:24.590
We appreciate your time.

